Package: gdscloud
Type: Package
Title: Cloud Storage Access for GDS Files
Version: 0.99.0
Date: 2026-05-12
Authors@R: person("Xiuwen", "Zheng", role=c("aut", "cre"),
    email="zhengx@u.washington.edu")
Description: Provides read-only access to GDS (Genomic Data Structure) files
    stored on cloud storage services including Amazon S3, Google Cloud Storage
    (GCS), and Azure Blob Storage, as well as any HTTP/HTTPS URL. Extends the
    'gdsfmt' package to transparently open GDS files from cloud URLs (http://,
    https://, s3://, gs://, az://) using efficient block caching and HTTP
    Range requests via libcurl.
Depends: R (>= 3.5.0), gdsfmt (>= 1.49.1)
LinkingTo: gdsfmt
Suggests: BiocStyle, knitr, rmarkdown, testthat
VignetteBuilder: knitr
License: GPL-3
SystemRequirements: libcurl (>= 7.28.0)
URL: https://github.com/zhengxwen/gdscloud
BugReports: https://github.com/zhengxwen/gdscloud/issues
biocViews: Infrastructure, DataImport
